{
  "texts": [
    "However, the table shows that each low-rank decomposition module offers a significant improvement in the overall performance of the multiple downstream tasks.Removing some of them can be used to achieve a different accuracy efficiency trade-off during training.",
    "Effect of Freezing Non-Attention Modules: As mentioned earlier in SubSection 3.4, besides fine-tuning the low-rank decomposition matrices, we unfreeze the patch embedding layer, the patch merging layer, the layer normalization, and the position bias in the attention layer.",
    "We analyze the effect of freezing these extra modules to provide insights into the accuracy-efficiency trade-off associated with each component.",
    "Table 3 shows the overall MTL accuracy (∆m) versus the number of trainable parameters when each of those modules is frozen.",
    "We can notice that unfreezing 5 shows the improvement in the accuracy of MTLoRA compared to single-task models."
  ]
}